1. unzip this somewhere
 * to run locally, do a 'npm install' before running 'node app.js'
2. do a "git init"
3. then do a "heroku create --stack cedar [name of your app]
4. then do a "git add ."
5. then do a "git commit -m "bla""
6. then do a "git push heroku master"

At this point, it should push to heroku, do all its magic and set you up to...

7. do a "heroku ps:scale web=1"

8. Now, do a "heroku open"

You should get your new Hello World web server, serving you requests in your browser. 

Enjoy!
